Hello,

My team is going to be using SDS Mark 4 Swerve Modules with NEOs for swerve drive.

We are going to be using Absolute CANCoders for the turning encoders, and Spark Relative Encoders (the NEO encoders on the module) for the drive encoders.

The main thing that I need help with is the SetDistancePerPulse and GetDistance from frc::Encoder. It appears that these are not in either of my encoders and it needs it for both turning and driving. (SwerveModule.cpp)

One thing that I thought might be similar is possibly this for the CANCoders, but I am unsure

Another thing that might be similar is this for the spark encoders but I am also unsure about this.

Here is our current code, based off of this example

Thanks
